        <mxCell id="k04SboY_8xgLOiQQaCqn-4" parent="k04SboY_8xgLOiQQaCqn-8" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=10;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;(1:*)&amp;nbsp; &lt;/b&gt;One-to-many. One source instance relates to many targets e.g. one organisation has many parties.&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;(1:0..1)&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp; One-to-zero-or-one. Optional one-to-one e.g. an organisation may or may not be an External organisation.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;(1:1)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt; Exactly one-to-one e.g. an invoice always generates exactly one EPR document.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;(*:1)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt; Many-to-one (no arrowhead on these) e.g. many producers can hold one PRN.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="250" x="10" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
